pull_request.title: Expose common Keccak symbol
pull_request.body: As discussed with @xvzcf. This exposes the `src/common` based Keccak used by Dilithium, Sphincs and Kyber in their AVX2 implementations and hides the Picnic variant.

pull_request.title: add OQS algs to auto-run list in speed
pull_request.body: Completes issue #35 : With this PR, `openssl speed` (without further parameters) also tests performance of all OQS algorithms automatically (as it does for classic crypto if called this way). Additional testing was not added for this as a) that would extend test time inappropriately and b) is not exactly essential functionality.

pull_request.title: Runtime detection in copy_from_pqclean
pull_request.body:
This is the 'generator' PR as discussed with @dstebila for more easy reading/understanding. The 'fulltest' variant (after running `copy_from_pqclean.py`) is also available at https://github.com/baentsch/liboqs/tree/copy-pqclean-v3-fulltest (CCI test run results at https://circleci.com/gh/baentsch/liboqs/tree/copy-pqclean-v3-fulltest).

I'd be glad for an initial review and statement as to whether you're OK converting this to a PR (plus the information who shall run the actual copy operation).

pull_request.title: Fix AddressSanitizer issues and enable in nightly runs
pull_request.body:
@christianpaquin Fixes a memory leak in Picnic2 that should be propagated upstream.

Fixes #604.

pull_request.title: Cleanup a few quirks in copy_from_pqclean
pull_request.body:
Deletes some object files that were accidentally added in 29232021b7ad5cd252a62cb192f2f023a8b2aad9

Sorts filenames where generating CMakeLists.  (I found that when I ran this locally, I got different output than what was in the files.  So I imagine that the order that the globbing returns is platform-dependent.  By sorting them, we should ensure that we don't get different orders each time we run it, minimizing changes in future checkins.)
